ARTICLE.TITLE: Suspect sought after late night stabbing
ARTICLE.TEXT:
CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas — Corpus Christi Police continue to search for a man accused in a stabbing early Wednesday morning.

Police were called to a home on Niagara Street near the Crosstown Expressway just before 3 a.m.

A 19-year-old man was found stabbed in the shoulder and another woman was found unconscious.

Police say it was a family argument that got out of hand, which led to the stabbing.

Both the man and woman were taken to the hospital, but are expected to be okay.

Police are now searching for the man responsible.

He faces a charge of aggravated assault.
